name: Chagos Islands
summary: In a historical development, the United Kingdom has agreed to return sovereignty of the Chagos Islands to Mauritius, ending a long-standing dispute. The Chagos Islands, once a British colony and currently hosts a secretive United States military base on Diego Garcia, will now be under the authority of Mauritius. This decision follows decades of negotiations and legal battles, with Mauritius claiming the islands as part of its territory. The agreement includes a deal to maintain the US military base, ensuring the UK's strategic interests in the region. This move represents a significant step in decolonization and marks the end of the UK's last African colony.
